ast.name: sphero turtle
ast.comment: A library to move a Sphero as if it was a turtle. #turtle #Sphero

body.text: Moves the turtle forward.

Turns the turtle by the specified angle. Angle is in degrees and can be either positive or negative. If the angle is positive, the turtle turns to its right. If it is negative, the turtle turns to its left.
Sets the color of the pen.
Maps the world coordinates to the board coordinates.
Turns clockwise by the specified angle in degrees
**Sphero turtle** is a library that emulates the LOGO environment to control a Sphero.
The user controls a virtual turtle that carries a pen. The turtle can move and turn. All the commands to the turtle are also sent to the Sphero ball.
### coordinates
The turtle world is centered on a portrait screen. x coordinates go from left to right and y coordinates go from bottom to top. The turtle starts at [0,0] pointing to the top of the screen.
### moving
Use `forward` to move the turtle forward.
You can also go backwards.
### turning

You can turn the turtle left (counter clockwise) or right (clockwise) by a certain amount of degrees. The turtle always starts pointing upwards. Note that the Sphero will not turn until you move forward or backward.
You can also use negative angles.
### customizing the pen
You can change the color of the pen
### mapping the world
